claim.claim-text:
A method of ectopically regenerating dental tissue, comprising steps of:
extirpating the pulp of a tooth of a first individual;
cutting out a predetermined length of the root portion of the tooth;
sealing one end of the root canal subjected to pulp extirpation;
injecting a root canal filling material containing mesenchymal stem cells and an extracellular matrix into the root canal; and
transplanting the root injected with the filling material into a second individual.
